Soohyeon: Ugh...!

Soohyeon: Guh... It's happening again... 
Seems to be acting up more and more recently.
Soohyeon: (This pendant must not be suppressing my symptoms enough...)
Soohyeon: (If I die, would mom be sad? Or would she be ashamed... that her daughter was a bewitcher?)
Soohyeon: No, stop thinking these thoughts. Just trust Li Hwa.
Soohyeon: Li Hwa's waiting for me!
Maeok: Soohyeon, what are you doing out and about again?
Soohyeon: Mom?
Maeok: Honestly, you're going to be someone's wife soon. You should learn to settle down, stop running around like a child.
Soohyeon: Come on, mom~ Why does getting married mean I can't run around like a kid anymore?
Soohyeon: Maybe it's because I'm getting married that I want to see all my friends again, talk to them while I still have the free time.
Soohyeon: No reason to get mad at me~
Maeok: *Sigh*...You think you've got it all figured out, huh? Don't care about what anybody else thinks... What if they laugh at you?
Soohyeon: (Ah... It's been so long since I've been able to hug mom like this)
Soohyeon: I don't care! They can laugh if they want!
Soohyeon: As long as I can give mom the best hugs...
Alliance Guard: Arbiter, Master Qing Feng and Master Toyokuni have arrived at the Alliance Hall.
Maeok: Well, that was fast.
Soohyeon: That's okay, mom. I'll see you later.
Maeok: Soohyeon... I promise once all this bewitcher trouble is over, I'll free up a few days for just me and you.
Maeok: In the meantime, it's dangerous outside. Please stop running around so much. You're getting me worried.
Soohyeon: Mom...
Soohyeon: Okay, mom. I understand. No need to worry!
Soohyeon: I hope... I hope we can help all the bewitchers get back to normal...
Soohyeon: Three bags of water root and five bags of frost weed, please.
Happy Merchant: Comin' right up! Just let me pack that up for ya'.
Weak Seahorse: Sir, please have some mercy... could you spare just a few strips of frost weed...?
Cool Merchant: You again!? Get out of here! Don't come back till you've got some money!
Weak Seahorse: I... I don't have any now, but I swear I'll pay you back!
Weak Seahorse: My child is sick, and my wife left me...
Cool Merchant: Well I'm runnin' a business here! If you don't stop begging for handouts, I'm gonna have to call the guards!
Weak Seahorse: But...
Cool Merchant: Get outta here! You're scarin' off the customers!
Happy Merchant: Sorry for the wait, miss. Here's your medicine.
Soohyeon: Actually, could you do me a favor?
Happy Merchant: Well, to think that'd you be such a generous young lady...
Happy Merchant: Alright, I'll have it delivered immediately!
Soohyeon: Thank you. Let me pay everything up front.
Happy Merchant: Hey, buddy. Here's the frost weed you wanted.
Weak Seahorse: Eh? But... Thank you! Thank you so much!
Weak Seahorse: How much do I owe you? I thought...
Happy Merchant: Don't thank me, thank that human girl. She got it for ya'.
Weak Seahorse: Human girl? Where did she go? I have to thank her!
Happy Merchant: Hmm... Looks like she went off toward Lake Illumina.
Weak Seahorse: Illumina? Thank you! Then I'll head there!
Li Hwa: Soohyeon, you're back! Good timing!
Soohyeon: What's wrong? You look anxious.
Li Hwa: Goldie was playing and she ran off. Meong Sa and I are looking for her.
Soohyeon: Then I'll help look!
Soohyeon: (Goldie... she must be lost.)
Soohyeon: Goldie!! Gold-
Weak Seahorse: Stay away!!
Weak Seahorse: Get out of here, you monsters!
Meong Sa: No, it's not what you think, I'm...
Weak Seahorse: I said get out of here! Don't hurt my child!
Meong Sa: Child...
Soohyeon: (I have to help!!)
Soohyeon: (But if I run over now, then they'll know I'm a bewitcher, too...)
Weak Seahorse: Take this!
Goldie: Oww!!
Weak Seahorse: Help me! Somebody, help!!
Soohyeon: Crap, he's gonna call the guards!
Meong Sa: ......
Goldie: Miss Soohyeon, I'm scared...
Soohyeon: (If I didn't just hesitate... I... I'm so selfish...)
Goldie: Miss Soohyeon?
Soohyeon: Don't be scared. We have to go back and tell Li Hwa!
